{
  "stem": "11723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we-- we had-- I should say, I had a charmed life before the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was easy, at least for me as a child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I traveled with my parents wherever they went.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at home, I had-- I can remember I had a charge account.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can you imagine?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A little three-year-old I was, and I had a charge account in the fanciest chocolate store on the Andrassy Avenue, in-- which is a wide boulevard similar to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what's the name of it, the one in Paris?",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Champs-Elysees?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Champs-Elysees, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Things don't come to me sometimes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Anyway, of course, it wasn't as nice as the Champs-Elysees, but it was very nice.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- I still remember, I used to go to these people called [NON-ENGLISH], that was their name.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I picked out whatever I wanted, and my father would pay the bill monthly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as I said, life went on OK.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all the restrictions, all the Jewish laws did not affect me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because when, for instance, Jews could no longer own businesses, my family had paid somebody called a straw man, they called him, who was a Christian who sold his or her name to Jews so that they could continue their businesses.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they got a small share of the profits, but business went on as usual.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in 1942, they started taking the Jewish men between the ages of 18 and 60, I believe.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had to be between the ages of 18 and 60 because my grandfathers, they were close to-- well, 50-- they were about 55, and they were still taken.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I'm assuming that it was up to 60.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they did take my Grandfather Gluck.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
